y=2x-4
y = \frac{2x}{4}
\frac{x}{4}=\frac{1}{4}x
 \begin{align} y & = \frac{2}{4} \\ \\ \iff y & = \frac{1}{2} + \;0 \\   &\quad\; \vdots \qquad\vdots \\ y & = m x + b \\ \\ \therefore m & = \frac 12; \quad b = 0 \\ \\ \therefore & (0, 0) \in \;\text{line} \\ \end{align} 
m = \; \text{slope} = \dfrac 12,\;\; (2, 1) \in \;\text{line}
m = \dfrac{ 1-0}{2 - 0} = \dfrac 12
 y=mx+n 
m
n=y-intercept
-n/m=x-intercept      
